ANKS TO HANSJORG SUBERKRUB: THE RETIREMENT OF A GREAT LIBRARIAN.     AFTER THE WAR SUBERKRUB STUDIED AT KIEL UNIVERSITY AND HAMBURG LIBRARY SCHOOL.HE WORKED IN KIEL LIBRARY FROM 1954-55 AND IN THE FOLLOWING YEAR BECAMEMUNICIPAL LIBRARIAN OF BIELEFELD, WHERE HE REMAINED, MODERNISING AND EXPANDINGLIBRARY SERVICES UNTIL HIS RETIREMENT IN OCT 81. SUBERKRUB HAS BEEN AN ACTIVEMEMBER OF MANY REGIONAL, NATIONAL AND INTERNATIONAL COMMITTEES, ESPECIALLY ASCHAIRMAN OF THE GERMAN LIBRARY ASSOCIATION FROM 1965 TO 1973. HE PLAYED ANIMPORTANT PART IN THE CREATION OF BIBLIOTHEKSPLAN '73, A SCHEME FOR DEVELOPINGGERMAN LIBRARIES AT NATIONAL LEVELS. SINCE 1973 HE HAS BEEN OCCUPIED WITHLIBRARIANSHIP IN NORTH RHINE WESTPHALIA, ADVANCED TRAINING FOR LIBRARIANS ANDAS CHAIRMAN OF THE STUDY GROUP ON LARGE MUNICIPAL LIBRARIES. HE IS A PROLIFICAND IMPORTANT AUTHOR ON LIBRARIANSHIP